{"LIXIVIAL":[{"def":"Impregnated with, or consisting of, alkaline salts extracted from wood ashes; impregnated with a salt or salts like a lixivium.","pos":""},{"def":"Of the color of lye; resembling lye.","pos":""}],"LIXIVIATE":[{"def":"To subject to a washing process for the purpose of separating soluble material from that which is insoluble; to leach, as ashes, for the purpose of extracting the alkaline substances.","pos":""}],"LIXIVIATION":[{"def":"Lixiviating; the process of separating a soluble substance form one that is insoluble, by washing with some solvent, as water; leaching.","pos":""}],"LIXIVIUM":[{"def":"A solution of alkaline salts extracted from wood ashes; hence, any solution obtained by lixiviation.","pos":""}]}